ABOUT:
Bacterial Blight is a major rice disease caused by Xanthomonas oryzae. It spreads through water, wind, and injuries on leaves.

SYMPTOMS:
Yellow to white leaf streaks
Leaves turning brown and drying
Bacterial ooze under humid conditions
"V" shaped drying from leaf tip

PREVENTION:
Use resistant varieties
Ensure proper water management
Remove infected plants early
Avoid field movement when plants are wet
